Q7miuh0aB4YjXLmiIp0wSg
This is a great location/building, and I want so much to like the food and the service, but things just don't seem to be getting any better. They are new, so we wanted to give them a chance to work out some of the kinks, but the food is just bland and effortless. The menu is also annoying. I'm fine with a detailed description of what will be in my dish, but I don't want to have to read out all of the ingredients to place my order. Name your dishes people! Last time we went, I ordered the "scrambled farm eggs, blue corn tortillas, radishes, queso fresco, avocado, pico de gallo, chile sauce..." and it was a pile of flavorless mush. The Bloody Mary's have also been pretty disgusting both times I've tried. Again, really wanted to like it, but it would take a lot for me to give it another try at this point.

