We've already been twice! Granted, we live just op the street. Everything we've tied has been delicious. My husband and I shared the salted cod tots and the crab dip featuring noble bread. Delicious. He had the cubano sandwich and I tried the carpaccio. Both were great. The cocktails are good too. We went just for drinks on Saturday and had a few of the bees knees and their version of a Moscow mule. Very refreshing, and I'm sure we'll be visiting again and again!

